# Files in the assets directory that must NOT be published.
#
# wrangler.jsonc sets `assets.directory: "."`, so by default every file in the
# repo root is uploaded as a servable asset — including the .git directory.
# On the build runner the repo is cloned (not exported), so .git is present and
# its packfile is read as an asset. Once that packfile passed 25 MiB it tripped
# the Workers per-asset size limit and every deploy failed with "Asset too
# large." Excluding .git here is what keeps the build green; do not remove it.
#
# Syntax is gitignore-style. Note this is separate from .gitignore: that
# controls what git tracks, this controls what Cloudflare serves.

# ── Required: version control internals ──
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# ── Repo tooling that should never be public ──
.github
.assetsignore
wrangler.jsonc
tools
apps-script
CLAUDE.md

# ── Local-only dirs. Already gitignored, so absent on the build runner, but
#    listed so a local `wrangler deploy --dry-run` matches CI instead of
#    failing on a large file that CI would never see. ──
.venv
node_modules
blogs-src
Extras
Resources
logs

# ── OS/editor noise ──
Thumbs.db
.DS_Store
*.swp
